            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Customer retention measures the percentage of accounts that renewed. Revenue retention (NRR) measures the percentage of revenue that renewed, including expansion. A company can have 90% customer retention but 110% NRR if existing customers upgraded enough to offset churned accounts.</p></div></div>
